title: lifting_body
body:
A lifting body is a fixed-wing aircraft or spacecraft configuration in which the body itself produces lift. In contrast to a flying wing, which is a wing with minimal or no conventional fuselage, a lifting body can be thought of as a fuselage with little or no conventional wing. Whereas a flying wing seeks to maximize cruise efficiency at subsonic speeds by eliminating non-lifting surfaces, lifting bodies generally minimize the drag and structure of a wing for subsonic, supersonic, and hypersonic flight, or, spacecraft re-entry.

Not to be confused with [[lifting]] or [[carrying]] tags.

h4. See also

title: byakko
body:
[b]Bai Hu[/b] (白虎) is the White Tiger, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. In Chinese culture, the tiger is the king of the beasts and has been presented with a 王 on his forehead for centuries. According to legend, the tiger's tail would turn white when it reached the age of 500 years. In this way, the white tiger became a kind of mythological creature. It was said that the white tiger would only appear when the emperor ruled with absolute virtue, or if there was peace throughout the world. It is known as Bai Hu in Chinese, Baek-ho in Korean, Byakko in Japanese and Bạch Hổ in Vietnamese. It represents the west and the autumn season.

h4. See also

* [[Seiryuu]], azure dragon of the east
* [[Genbu]], black tortoise of the north
* [[Suzaku]], vermilion bird of the south

title: genbu
body:
[b]Xuan Wu[/b] (玄龜) is the Black Tortoise/Black Turtle, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. Despite its English name, it is usually depicted as a turtle entwined together with a snake. Further, in East Asia, it is not called after either animal but is instead known as the "Black Warrior" under various local pronunciations. It is known as Xuan Wu (or sometimes Xuan Gui) in Chinese, Hyeon-mu in Korean, Genbu in Japanese and Huyền Vũ in Vietnamese. It represents the north and the winter season.

h4. See also

* [[Seiryuu]], azure dragon of the east

[b]Qing Long[/b] (青龍) is the Azure Dragon, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. It should not be confused with the mythological yellow dragon that is associated with the Emperor of China. It is also referred to in media, feng shui, other cultures, and in various venues as the Green Dragon and the Avalon Dragon. It is known as Qing Long in Chinese, Cheong-ryong in Korean, Seiryuu in Japanese and Thanh Long in Vietnamese. It represents the east and the spring season.

title: suzaku
body:
[b]Zhu Que[/b] (朱雀) is the Vermilion Bird, one of the "Four Symbols":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Symbols_%28China%29 of the Chinese constellations. It is described as a red bird that resembles a pheasant with a five-colored plumage and is perpetually covered in flames. It is often mistaken for the Fenghuang due to similarities in appearance, but the two are different creatures. It is known as Zhu Que (or sometimes Zhu Qiao) in Chinese, Ju-jak in Korean, Suzaku/Shujaku in Japanese and Chu Tước in Vietnamese. It represents the south and the summer season.

title: wilhelm_burgdorf
body:
Wilhelm Burgdorf (15 February 1895 – 2 May 1945) was one of 4 generals in the OKH's Chief of Staff, and held the post of Chief of the Army Personnel Office (Heerespersonalamt) and Chief Adjutant to Adolf Hitler. Historians have noted that Burgdorf in the latter stages of the war consumed alcohol heavily and got angry very easily.

After failed surrender negotiations he attempted to shoot Hans Fritzsche after the latter intended to surrender to Soviet Marshall Georgy Zhukov. On May 2nd 1945 he and his colleague Hans Krebs commited suicide in the Führerbunker.

He is portrayed by Justus von Dohnányi in the 2004 movie Der Untergang.

He appears in the second cour of the series, still bitter over the events of the manga and joining [[altair (re:creators)|Altair]]'s faction purely to take him down.

title: hans_krebs
body:
Hans Krebs (March 4th 1898 - May 2nd 1945) was a Wehrmacht general and one of 4 generals in the OKH's Chief of Staff (the others being Keitel, Jodl and Burgdorf.)

He was the one who opened surrender negotiations after the suicide of Hitler, but due to the refusal of Goebbels to adhere to terms of unconditional surrender they ended with no agreement and soon after; on May 2nd 1945, Krebs and Burgdorf commited suicide in the Führerbunker.

He is portrayed by Rolf Kanies in the 2004 movie, Der Untergang.

title: css_virginia
body:
Cribbed from Conway's all the World's Fighting Ships 1860-1905:
The first Virginia set the pattern for Confederate armoured ships, with the forward and after parts of the hull awash except for a low coaming at the bows, and a castmate with inclined sides rising amidships. The lower edge of the casemate was only 6in below water, a foot less than intended, and after the fight with Monitor the hull below was increased to 3in for 160ft from below the bows for a depth of 3 1/2ft. The 7in guns were fore and aft in the casemate, each with three ports, the other guns at the sides and the howitzers fore and aft on the casemate roof, where the 3in or 4in pilot-house was also located forward. The famous drawn battle with the monitor was fought on 9.3.1862 but when the Virginia reappeared on 11.4.1862 the Monitor declined to engage her. On the abandonment of Norfolk, the Confederates burnt Virginia as her draught was too deep to ascend the James River.

title: maehara_shinobu
body:
Shinobu is the youngest resident of the Hinata Lodge at the beginning of [[Love Hina]], being only 12 years old at the start of the manga and 13 in the anime.  She has a quiet and shy personality, and is prone to self doubting herself. Shinobu is quite skilled at cooking and is typically the one preparing the meals at the Hinata Lodge. She also does most of the chores around Hinata Lodge, and is frequently shown taking care of the residents' laundry.  Unlike the rest of the residents at Hinata Lodge, Shinobu is not prone to hitting [[urashima keitarou|Keitaro]], but is instead prone to getting emotional and crying in response to Keitaro's actions and mishaps.  

Her birthday is November 15th.

title: ez_do_dance
body:
A Jpop song by TRF, released in 1993. It's become the subject of many covers by other Jpop groups and [[idol]]s.

A cover of the song was used as the second opening theme for the third season of the [i][[Pretty Rhythm]][/i] anime, [i][[Pretty Rhythm Rainbow Live]][/i]. The song makes a return in the first [i][[King of Prism by Prettyrhythm]][/i] as a remix sung by [[Yamato Alexander]] and [[Nishina Kazuki]]. 

The [i]King of Prism [/i] rendition is known for the distinctive outfit Alexander and Kazuki (and later [[Kougami Taiga]]) wear: a skimpy white/black [[bodysuit]] with their motif color as [[neon trim]].

h4.See also

* "Original Video (Youtube)":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LKEWlU4rkxc]

title: eyelash_curler
body:
An eyelash curler is a hand-operated mechanical device which has a set of grips that operate a clamp. The grips are held and used similar to scissor grips. They are, unsurprisingly, used to curl eyelashes. They're typically made of steel.

An eyelash curler should not be confused with a [[mascara]] applicator (sometimes called a wand) which has short bristles on a small stick and typically has a colorful plastic handle. As a general rule-of-thumb, if it doesn't look like a medieval torture device, it's probably not an eyelash curler.

body: The hapless protagonist of [[ore no nounai sentakushi ga gakuen love-comedy wo zenryoku de jama shiteiru|NouCome]]. He was a normal schoolboy until he was stricken by the curse of Absolute Choice. Now that he's in high-school, everyone thinks he's a freak.

title: chocolat_(noucome)
body: Amakusa's 'helper' in [[ore no nounai sentakushi ga gakuen love-comedy wo zenryoku de jama shiteiru|NouCome]], so named because she has a bad case of amnesia and so came up with her new name based on what she happened to be eating at the time. Chocolat is supposed to help Amakusa rid himself of the "Absolute Choice" curse but she is highly ineffectual and mostly serves to annoy Amakusa even more. Has a very happy-go-lucky attitude, a tendency to act like a puppy and an almost superhuman ability to receive sweets from people.

title: douraku_utage
body: Utage is the teacher of Amakusa Kanade in [[ore no nounai sentakushi ga gakuen love-comedy wo zenryoku de jama shiteiru|NouCome]]. Despite looking like a little girl with red-pink hair, she is actually 29 years old when the story begins. Utage was afflicted by the same curse as Kanade in the past and thus is one of the few people who can truly relate to his miserable life, which is why she tries to help him provided he does not anger her.

title: hakoniwa_yuragi
body: Yuragi, a character from [[ore no nounai sentakushi ga gakuen love-comedy wo zenryoku de jama shiteiru|NouCome]], is a serial little sister. She appears to have a compulsive urge to 'collect' as many older brothers and sisters as she can, going so far as to hunt for them on her days off. Any strangers she makes acquaintance with can expect to be asked "Can I call you big brother / sister?", even if the person in question is younger than her. Despite this, she claims that Amakusa is her only 'true' big brother.

title: yukihira_furano
body:
One of Amakusa's classmates in [[ore no nounai sentakushi ga gakuen love-comedy wo zenryoku de jama shiteiru|NouCome]], Yukihira seems to enjoy abusing Amakusa both verbally and physically as often as possible. Her habitual demeanour is very calm and collected, her face very rarely showing any kind of emotion. It is entirely possible, however, that this coolness is a carefully constructed facade for her true personality: a highly shy girly-girl with a weakness for cute things.

She has short silver hair, red-purple eyes, and wears a [[sheep hair ornament]].

A multimedia project about the idol group Shounen Hollywood and their rise to fame.

Started as a screenplay which was tuned into a novel in 2012 about the original "SHOUNEN HOLLYWOOD" group. Received a sequel in the 2014 anime [i]Shounen Hollywood -HOLLY STAGE FOR 49-[/i]/[i]-HOLLY STAGE FOR 50-[/i], which takes place 15 years after the original novel with a new generation of the group, and received a sequel in turn in the form of the web serial "[i]Shounen Hollywood -HOLLY STAGE FOR 51-[/i]", exclusive only to the fanclub of the series. A manga of the series, "HOLLY TRIP FOR YOU", ran in 2014.

The group exists as a defictionalized band titled "ZEN THE HOLLYWOOD", beginning in 2013.

title: suou_tsukasa
body:
[i][[Ensemble Stars!]][/i] character. A first year student and member of [[knights (ensemble stars!)|Knights]]. 

He has [[short hair|short]] [[red hair]] and [[purple eyes]]. At school, he wears the standard [[yumenosaki school uniform|Yumenosaki uniform]], consisting on [[plaid pants]], a [[blazer]] and [[necktie]]. For Knights, he wears [[black gloves]], [[striped pants]] and a [[white shirt]] with [[epaulettes]].

Serious and composed, Tsukasa speaks in a manner rather mature for his age. He comes from a rich family and is always talking about elegance. He speaks fluent English and has a love for "commoner sweets". Tsukasa also believes the rest of the Knights look down on him because he's the youngest. He also does not get along with the leader [[tsukinaga leo|Leo Tsukinaga]], but comes to respect him over time.

Tsukasa becomes very smitten with [[anzu (ensemble stars!)|Anzu]] at the beginning of the story and calls her "Onee-sama". He doesn't like when other first-years students act too close or friendly with her.

title: marine_corps
body:
Also known as [b]naval infantry[/b]. A [b]marine corps[/b] is a force of naval infantry designed for amphibious and ship to shore air assault, often as the beginning stages of an invasion, and as a quick reactionary force to protect a country's interests overseas. It uses the mobility and logistics of a navy to be able to quickly project ground forces into a conflict. 

A marine corps can range from a small special operations unit, such as the Royal Marines, to an entire combined arms military branch, like the United States Marine Corps with infantry, armor, air (both fixed and rotary wing), and support such as supply, logistics, transport, and communications. 

Marine corps often stress combat proficiency for all members, not just in combat occupations, because in the confusion of an initial assault, the rear echelons may come under attack and a defender may try to destroy an initial beachhead by attacking their supplies being brought to shore. 

Modern marine corps evolved from naval infantry aboard sailing vessels whose primary roles were to protect a ship from boarding, board enemy vessels, and to protect the command crew in the event of mutiny. Later, during the later half of the 19th century, imperial powers soon found a need for ground forces that could quickly react to protect their overseas interests. Therefor many marine corps grew in order to fulfill this role. 

Also, during this time with the increasing power and range of naval guns, boarding become a less common naval tactic to use in war, and the end of impressment (conscription) to crew ships meant a reduced the risk of mutiny. Marine corps evolved so that their primary mission now was amphibious assault and protection of overseas interests.
